Description: Up for bids here is a Fender Thin Line Telecaster electric guitar project. Fender Squier Mahogany Thin Line loaded body has been mated with MIM era Maple Neck and aftermarket Tone Rider Alnico II soap bar pick up. C shaped Maple neck is straight and plays great, action is good and neck is clean. Dimensions are 1 5/8” inches at the top nut and 2 3/16” inches at the base with 21 frets in decent condition with some wear at 2nd and 3rd fret area. Modern Fender In-line tuners are installed, with classic headstock that shows one micro scuff mark at the top of the rounded section and the neck has a small eyelash shaped nick on the back at 10th fret, see pics for condition. Original single coil pickup in rear position, neck pickup is an aftermarket Tone Rider Vintage 90 Alnico II Soap Bar pickup which is installed and wired through a separate tone control. Pearloid pick guard is now equipped with two tone controls and a regular volume control. An extra tone pot circuit was added to this pick guard to create individual tone controls for each pick up. All hardware is secured with set nuts, pots and switches hand soldered and mounted securely in the Fender Squier Thin Line body with super polished gloss finish. Guitar is fully built, working and completed as a pet project which turned into my 7th guitar, which is 2 guitars too many according to my wife. This is a truly unique instrument for the player who does not want just another "Thin Line Tele", and at an affordable “No Reserve” price. Guitar will be packed in sturdy cardboard box wrapped in a Fender Gig Bag. I offer No Returns so be sure you are ready to buy when bidding, and usually ship via UPS Ground or USPS (more affordable to non-urban buyers) to anywhere in the United States. I will gladly pay for tracking, insurance and shipping confirmation. Winning bidder to make payment within 5 days. Bidder notice, your bid is a binding commitment to purchase and pay in a timely manner. Good Luck bidding and check out my other auctions for more cool collectibles and electronics. 8^)=
